Definition: lacking even the rudiments of courage
Example: abjectly fearful; the craven fellow turned and ran; a craven proposal to raise the white flag; this recreant knight- Spenser
Synonyms: noun, attribute, cravenness, recreant, person, lacking, even, the, rudiments, of, courage, abjectly, fearful, fellow, turned, and, ran, a, proposal, to, raise, white, flag, this, knight, -, Spenser
Category: adj.all
